; Regression test for issue #763: Error: Cannot convert a balance with
; multiple commodities to an amount (BZ#763)
;
; When a register report uses -H together with a display filter that
; references `commodity` (e.g., -d "commodity == 'EUR'") on a journal
; containing multiple commodities, get_commodity() was called for a
; posting whose compound value was a multi-commodity balance and tried
; to convert that balance to an amount, throwing "Cannot convert a
; balance with multiple commodities to an amount".
;
; The fix extends the sequence guard in get_commodity() (and the parallel
; get_commodity_is_primary()) to also handle multi-commodity balances:
; when the compound value is a balance holding more than one commodity,
; fall back to post.amount's commodity, which matches what a -l filter
; already sees.

2011-01-01 * Opening balance
    Assets:Investments           1 "BBB" @  2.653329339867 GBP
    Equity:Opening balance

2011-01-10 * Fee
    Liabilities:Credit Card                         -2.83 EUR
    Expenses:Fees                                 (2.83/2 EUR)
    Assets:Receivable

test reg -X EUR -H -l "commodity == 'EUR'"
11-Jan-10 Fee                   Liabilitie:Credit Card    -2.83 EUR    -2.83 EUR
                                <Adjustment>              -0.01 EUR    -2.84 EUR
                                Expenses:Fees              1.42 EUR    -1.42 EUR
                                Assets:Receivable          1.42 EUR            0
end test

test reg -X EUR -H -d "commodity == 'EUR'"
11-Jan-10 Fee                   Liabilitie:Credit Card    -2.83 EUR        1 BBB
                                                                       -2.83 EUR
                                GBP-2.653329339867000000000000000000000000000000
                                Expenses:Fees              1.42 EUR        1 BBB
                                                                       -1.42 EUR
                                GBP-2.653329339867000000000000000000000000000000
                                Assets:Receivable          1.42 EUR        1 BBB
                                GBP-2.653329339867000000000000000000000000000000
end test
